The paper deals with immunization strategies for complex networks, which is a topic that falls under the scope of several arXiv CS sub-categories. 

- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on community structure, which is a key feature of social networks. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is also a possible category as the paper proposes and investigates different immunization strategies, which can be seen as software engineering solutions for controlling epidemics in networks. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper uses the Susceptible-Infected-Removed (SIR) epidemiological model to conduct numerical simulations, which is a system and control approach to studying epidemics. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is a possible category as the paper deals with network topology and connectivity, which are key aspects of networking and internet architecture. 
- cs.SOC (Computational Social Science) is also a possible category as the paper uses social network analysis techniques to study the community structure of networks and its impact on epidemic control.
